AC  GenProp0112
DE  Riboflavin, FAD and FMN from GTP and ribulose-5-P
TP  PATHWAY
AU  Haft DH
TH  2
DC  Riboflavin Biosynthesis (early stages)
DR  IUBMB; misc; riboflavin1;
DC  Riboflavin Biosynthesis (late stages)
DR  IUBMB; misc; riboflavin2;
DC  FAD Biosynthesis
DR  IUBMB; misc; FAD;
CC  Flavin-adenine dinucleotide (FAD) is synthesized via
CC  flavinmononucleotide (FMN) and riboflavin (vitamin B2) from GTP,
CC  ribulose-5-phosphate and ATP in a 9-step pathway. FAD and FMN are
CC  important carriers of hydrogen and electrons which are usually found
CC  tightly bound or covalently linked to enzymes such as dehydrogenases,
CC  oxidases and monooxygenases. The pathway in bacteria and archaea/fungi
CC  varies slightly with the order in which a pair of reductase and
CC  deaminase steps take place.
**  The KEGG entry for step 5, riboflavin synthase, EC 2.5.1.9, is
**  apparently in error, subsuming step 4 (which does not have an EC#) and
**  representing that incorrectly to boot. (1/05, JDS)
**  Evidence for steps 2 and 3 is the same.
